timestamps.description: Thomas Abernathy is lying in the hospital bed, appears to be breathing with some effort. His chest is rising and falling noticeably. Nasal cannula is in place.
The patient's facial expression suggests anxiety. He is starting to move his arms a bit erratically. Breathing remains labored with visible chest retractions.
Thomas Abernathy begins to show signs of chest discomfort, possibly chest pain.  He is holding up his hands in distress, facial expression of anxiety intensifies. Breathing labored.
Patient exhibits increased signs of distress, possibly due to chest pain. He's grasping and gasping for air. Labored breathing is very prominent.

description: Thomas Abernathy, a 62-year-old male with pre-existing conditions including hypertension, type 2 diabetes, coronary artery disease and COPD, presents with acute myocardial infarction, initially shows signs of labored breathing, progressing to chest pain and anxiety. His distress increases throughout the observation period.
